bilingual.source: I like noodles and I like meat.
There isn't any meat in the fridge.

list.abstract: meat（[miːt]），英语单词。其属于名词，释义为肉，实质，可食用部分等。相关短语搭配：eat meat（吃肉）。例句：We haven't got any meat for dinner.（我们晚餐没有肉了。） meat作名词时的近义词有flesh、carne。 meat的复数形式为meats。

yingyinNormal.en: So the baby is totally craving meat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 宝宝想肉想疯了。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. Some eat meat, some eat vegetable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 确实，有人吃肉，也有人吃素。

yingyinNormal.en: What's the sauce? Is it meat based? No. Eat now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是什么酱，是肉酱吗？不是的，快吃吧。

yingyinNormal.en: You're gonna cut her meat for her, too, there, Cal?
yingyinNormal.zh: 卡尔，你要帮她切肉吗?

yingyinNormal.en: This afternoon I tried tricking it, I made it a soy-burger to make it think it was getting meat, you know? And I got nauseous.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下午我想用素肉堡骗他，让他以为他吃到肉结果就反胃了。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, fine. Just the sword, 210. Thank you. I can eat meat this week.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，就这把剑，二百一。谢谢，这周有肉吃啦。

yingyinNormal.en: And for our suddenly "back on the Hindu wagon" Raj, the meat lover's pizza, no meat. Coming right up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 给我们突然回到印度饮食习惯的拉杰的，是专给爱吃肉的人准备的披萨，不放肉，马上就来。

yingyinNormal.en: I reluct meat. It's no meat, Reggie. Yes, but is this brown sauce vegetarian, Esa? Yes, I tell you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不喜欢吃肉。那不是肉，雷吉。但这个酱汁是棕色的，而我是素食主义者，埃萨。是的，我说是的。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it's nice. Yeah. You could just slice through the meat and then onto the other side.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很不错。是的，把肉切开，一直切到底。

yingyinNormal.en: We make fire. Cook meat. Then put out fire by peeing, no get invited back.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们生火煮肉，然后撒尿熄火，从此成为被拒绝的客人。

yingyinNormal.en: Apparently, you did not know that the chef's salad is kitchen trickery to utilize scrap meat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 显然，你不知道推荐沙拉是食堂的杂碎肉骗人把戏。

yingyinNormal.en: And there's a bit of the brown meat as well, because that's the brains. And so this is what we want to discard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有些棕色的肉，这是大脑。我们要扔掉这些。

yingyinNormal.en: And you can use any other cooking wine, but I love Shao Hsing, from the Shao Hsing region in China. Just gives this gorgeous, bitter-sweet edge to any dish, and it just takes the rawness of meat or fish, and any odours off meat and fish.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你也可以使用其他料酒，但我爱用绍兴，中国绍兴地区产的绍兴米酒，可以让菜肴变得鲜美，苦中带甜，而且可以令肉或鱼更加入味，还能去除肉的腥味。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't want to lose the meat that's in the middle cos that's really juicy and that's the best bits.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不要浪费中间的肉，因为这些肉汁很多，是最好吃的部分。

yingyinNormal.en: When he does, it's always with this disappointed scowl, like someone skimped on the meat in his sandwich.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我每次跟他讲话，他就像吃到没夹肉的三明治那样失望。

yingyinNormal.en: Dinner's almost ready. If you like meatloaf, I'm sure you'll like its cousin, bowl of meat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 晚餐快好了，如果你们喜欢烘肉卷，那肯定会喜欢它的表亲，大碗肉。

yingyinNormal.en: Remember when we would track blood ox through the Frostwind dunes? There is always meat. Always life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还记得那是我们穿过霜风沙丘去捕杀血牛？总是有肉吃，蛊然生机。

yingyinNormal.en: So, who's the mystery man? Well, he's a doctor. A real doctor? No, a doctor of meat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那个神秘男子是谁？他是个医生（跟“博士”同词）。真正的医生？不，他是研究肉的。

yingyinNormal.en: And this bit is the tail of the crab, so we just snap that bit off, because it's not very tasty, there's no meat there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这部分是螃蟹的尾巴，扯下来就好，因为它不太好吃，没有肉。

yingyinNormal.en: And then I need a hot wok. Crack the crab claws but leave the meat in the claws. Roughly chop a chilli.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然后我要把锅烧热。敲碎蟹爪，但把肉留在爪子里。粗粗地切碎一只辣椒。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: According to a report on UK food production, 85 percent of the country's total land area is associated with <highlight>meat</highlight> and dairy production.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据一份关于英国食品生产的报告，英国85%的土地与肉类和奶制品的生产有关。

examination_example.sentence: So even covering the whole country in livestock farms wouldn't allow us to cover all our <highlight>meat</highlight> and dairy needs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以即使畜牧业覆盖全国，也不能满足我们对肉类和奶制品的需求。

examination_example.sentence: There, as people got more money, some of them may have more cleared land for cattle to raise for <highlight>meat</highlight>, Ferraro says.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 费拉罗说，在那里，随着人们赚的钱更多，一些人可能会有更多的空地饲养牲畜，提供肉类。

examination_example.sentence: This is because they are sometimes hunted for their <highlight>meat</highlight> or their skin.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是因为它们有时会被猎杀，来获取肉或皮。

examination_example.sentence: The common prescription is to primarily shop the grocery store, since that's where fresh produce, <highlight>meat</highlight> and seafood, and dairy are.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通常的做法是主要在杂货店购物，因为那里有新鲜农产品、肉类、海鲜和乳制品。

examination_example.sentence: A growing number of people wanting to move up the food chain to consume highly grain-intensive <highlight>meat</highlight> products.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 越来越多的人想要向食物链的上层移动，消费高度谷物密集型的肉类产品。

word_usage.usage: 该词的含义为“供食用的肉”，鱼肉应用fish，其他各类的肉各有专名，如猪肉、羊肉、牛肉、鸡肉分别为：pork、mutton、beef、 chicken。 flesh指人和脊椎动物的肌肉组织，区别于骨、皮。
